# BizInsights — Project Overview

BizInsights is a local-first, universal **data analyzer**.  
Upload a file → it auto-cleans, detects schema and domain, then produces an **executive summary**, **KPIs**, and **interactive charts** (dark theme).

---

## Purpose

- **Speed up the “first look”** on a new dataset (CSV, Excel, Parquet, JSON, XML)
- Provide **explainable** insights and KPIs you can copy into reports
- Serve as a **portfolio-quality** reference for end-to-end data work
- Run **entirely on your machine** (no external services)

---

## What it does

1. **Ingest**: robust reader for CSV/TSV/Excel/Parquet/JSON/XML  
2. **Clean**: normalizes nulls, strips commas, parses `%` strings, fixes mixed types  
3. **Detect**: identifies date/amount/percent/categorical columns + **domain** (e.g., Sales vs. Churn)  
4. **Analyze**: computes KPIs (totals/averages), trend slope, momentum (last 3 vs prior 3), best/worst months, top segments  
5. **Visualize**: monthly trend + top dimension charts (Chart.js, dark UI)  
6. **Export**: one-click **PNG** (charts) and **JSON** (full analysis payload)

---

## Supported file formats

- **CSV**, **TSV**, **Excel** (`.xlsx`/`.xls`), **Parquet** (`fastparquet`), **JSON**, **XML`**  
- *(Feather is optional and disabled by default; enable via `pyarrow` if desired.)*

---

## Domains & example insights

| Domain           | Typical columns detected                         | KPIs & Insights (examples)                                                                 |
|------------------|---------------------------------------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| **Sales / Retail** | Date, Category/Segment, Sales, Profit, Discount  | Total/avg sales, trend slope per month, seasonal spikes, top category, margin, momentum    |
| **Subscriptions / Churn** | customerID, tenure, MonthlyCharges, Churn | ARPU/ACPU, churn rate, top churned segments, tenure distribution                           |
| **Education**     | date, course, score/grade                        | avg score, completion rate, trend of submissions                                           |
| **IoT / Telemetry** | timestamp, device, metric                      | uptime/avg reading, anomalies by window, device leaderboard                                 |
| **Reviews / NLP (light)** | date, rating, text (optional)              | avg rating by month/segment, volume spikes                                                 |

> The analyzer is designed to give **useful first-pass insights** on datasets up to ~10⁵ rows on a laptop. For heavier workloads, treat this as a staging/EDA step.

---

## Use cases

- Rapid **EDA** before deeper modeling
- **Portfolio/demo** app for interviews
- Internal **BI “first read”** on new CSV drops
- Quick **data cleaning & validation** (nulls, types, %/currency parsing)
- **Feature ideation**: trend/momentum/seasonality & segment KPIs

---

## Tech stack

- **Backend:** Python 3.x, **Flask**, **Pandas**, **NumPy**
- **Storage/IO:** `openpyxl` (Excel), **fastparquet** (Parquet)
- **Frontend:** HTML/CSS + **Chart.js** (dark theme)
- **Exports:** PNG (charts), JSON (analysis payload)

### Skills demonstrated

- Data wrangling & type inference  
- ETL-style cleaning (nulls, numeric strings, percentages)  
- Time-series KPIs (trend slope via linear fit, momentum windows)  
- Segmentation & top-N analysis  
- Flask routing, templating, and error handling  
- Client-side charting with Chart.js

